trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> objects.

The <xref:System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping> class provides a mapping between the namespace specified in your [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] binding source and a prefix you specify that you can use in [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)].
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection"></xref> class.
Adds a <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object to this collection.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object to add.
This cannot be `null`.
If mapping is `null`.
If the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping.Uri"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object is `null`.
Adds a <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object to this collection.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object to add.
This cannot be `null`.
If mapping is `null`.
Adds a text string as a child of this <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection"></xref> object.
The text string to add as a child.
If text is `null`.
Removes all <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> objects in this collection.
This is potentially an expensive operation; consider just creating a new <xref:System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection> object.
Returns a value that indicates whether this collection contains the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object of interest.
This cannot be `null`.
`true` if this collection contains the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object; otherwise, `false`.
If mapping is `null`.
If the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping.Uri"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object is `null`.
Copies the items of the collection to the specified array, starting at the specified index.
The array that is the destination of the items copied from the collection.
The zero-based index in array at which copying starts.
If array is `null`.
If the number of items exceed the length of the array.
Gets the number of <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> objects in the collection.
The number of <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> objects in the collection.
Returns an <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> object that you can use to enumerate the items in this collection.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> object that you can use to enumerate the items in this collection.
Gets a value that indicates whether this collection is read-only.
This always returns `false`.
Returns a generic <xref href="System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator`1"></xref> object.
This is a protected member that is for <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> implementations.
A generic <xref href="System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator`1"></xref> object.
Removes the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object from this collection.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object to remove.
This cannot be `null`.
`true` if the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object has been successfully removed; otherwise, `false`.
If mapping is `null`.
If the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping.Uri"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMapping"></xref> object is `null`.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable`1.GetEnumerator"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> interface.
An <xref href="System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator`1"></xref> object that can be used to iterate through the collection.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.IAddChild.AddChild(System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Windows.Markup.IAddChild> interface.
The child <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to add.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.IAddChild.AddText(System.String)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Data.XmlNamespaceMappingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Windows.Markup.IAddChild> interface.
The text to add to the <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
